examples.en: He harangued us for hours about the evils of popular culture.
He delivered a long harangue about the evils of popular culture.
The eminent professor harangued for three hours on his favorite subject, the clash of East and West.
He stood on the street corner, haranguing passers-by about the stupidity of the forthcoming war.
She launched into a long harangue about poor customer service without realizing that I wasn't even an employee!
